# Implementation Plan - Let's Exercise (一起運動吧)

This plan outlines the steps to implement the "Let's Exercise" feature, a campus sports partner matching system.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> This feature heavily reuses the logic from "Let's Go Out" (Travel) as requested, but tailors the UI and categories specifically for sports.

## Proposed Changes

### Logic & Routing

#### [NEW] [sports.js](file:///c:/Users/User/OneDrive/Desktop/Joinup/js/views/sports.js)
- Create a new view file based on [travel.js](file:///c:/Users/User/OneDrive/Desktop/Joinup/js/views/travel.js).
- **Key Changes**:
    - Update title to "一起運動吧".
    - Update `CATEGORY_ID` to `'sports'`.
    - **Activity Types**: Customize dropdown options to focus on sports (Basketball, Badminton, Gym, Jogging, Tennis, Volleyball, etc.).
    - **Locations**: customize default meeting points (Gym, Track, Basketball Courts, Swimming Pool).

#### [MODIFY] [app.js](file:///c:/Users/User/OneDrive/Desktop/Joinup/js/app.js)
- Add routing logic for the `sports` key.
- Dynamically import `sports.js` and call `renderSports()`.

#### [MODIFY] [mockStore.js](file:///c:/Users/User/OneDrive/Desktop/Joinup/js/models/mockStore.js)
- Add `joinSportsActivity` method (cloned/aliased from [joinTravelActivity](file:///c:/Users/User/OneDrive/Desktop/Joinup/js/models/mockStore.js#485-541)) to ensure consistent data handling for the new category.
- Ensure [getPosts](file:///c:/Users/User/OneDrive/Desktop/Joinup/js/models/mockStore.js#112-135) correctly filters by `sports` category.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1.  **Navigation**: Click "一起運動吧" on the home page and verify it loads the new landing page.
2.  **Create Post**:
    - Create a new "Basketball" activity.
    - Verify it appears in the list.
    - Check local storage to ensure `category` is saved as `'sports'`.
3.  **Join Activity**:
    - Use a different user (or incognito/simulated user) to join the activity.
    - Verify instant join works (no approval required, matching Travel behavior).
    - Verify Chat works.
